<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON THE COVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The curtain rises for Broadway's best at the 43rd annual presentation of "The 
Tony Awards" Sunday at 9 p.m. on CBS (Channels 2 and 8). 
</P>
<P>
For the third year in a row, four-time Tony winner Angela Lansbury will preside 
over the event recognizing theatrical achievement. 
</P>
<P>
The cover features five of the productions nominated for top honors. Clockwise 
from upper left, they are: Bill Irwin in "Largely New York"; Pauline Collins in 
"Shirley Valentine"; Gabriel Barre, left, and Brian Lane Green in "Starmites"; 
Joan Allen in "The Heidi Chronicles," and Philip Bosco and Jane Connell in 
"Lend Me a Tenor." 
</P>
<P>
With the exception of "Starmites," a nominee for best musical along with "Black 
and Blue" and "Jerome Robbins' Broadway," the productions have been nominated 
for best play. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, COLOR, THE TONYS -- Broadway's best share the spotlight Sunday on CBS. 
Among the productions up for top honors, closkwise from upper left, at the 43rd 
annual ceremony: "Largely New York"; "Shirley Valentine"; the musical 
"Starmites"; "The Heidi Chronicles," and "Lend Me a Tenor." 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
