<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOVIES TO TAPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Laura (AMC Sunday at 9:45 p.m.): The cop who falls in love with the socialite 
murder victim. A great film noir, directed by Otto Preminger. (1:45) 
</P>
<P>
El Sur (Bravo Monday at 8 p.m.): A beautiful 1983 psychological study of an 
abandoned girl in the provinces, by the superb contemporary Spanish director, 
Victor Erice. (2:00) 
</P>
<P>
Seven Women (Channel 13 Tuesday at 1:30 a.m.): John Ford's last film, with Anne 
Bancroft and Margaret Leighton among a septet of women besieged at a Chinese 
mission. One of his masterpieces. (2:00) 
</P>
<P>
Four by Godard (Bravo Wednesday at 6:30, 8:30, 10 &amp; 11:30 p.m.): An evening 
with the great, iconoclastic French film maker, Jean-Luc Godard. Four films 
from his '60s heyday: "Alphaville," "Les Carabiniers," "Le Petit Soldat" and 
"Breathless." 
</P>
<P>
Heart Like a Wheel (Channel 11 Friday at 8 p.m.): Bonnie Bedelia takes home the 
trophies (or should have) in Jonathan Kaplan's feisty bio of drag-race champ 
Shirley Muldowney. (2:00) 
</P>
<P>
Once Upon a Time in the West (Channel 11 Saturday at midnight): In memoriam: 
Sergio Leone (1929-1989). (3:00) 
</P>
</TEXT>
