<HEADLINE>
<P>
PASADENA PLEASURES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
They used to say Pasadena doesn't have any good restaurants. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Crocodile Cafe, 140 S. Lake Ave., Pasadena. (818) 449-9900. Style: Poor man's 
Parkway Grill. Setting: The Croc That Roared. Recommended dishes: Grilled 
chicken skewer with two chutneys; chicken fettuccine with vegetable sauce; 
cheeseburger. Cost per person: $8-$20. 
</P>
<P>
Dodsworth Bar &amp; Grill, 2 W. Colorado Blvd., Pasadena. (818) 578-1344. 
Style: A little something of everything to suit everybody. Setting: Upscale 
faculty lounge. Recommended dishes: Pork tostada; veal scaloppine with fresh 
ginger. Cost per person: $15-$30. 
</P>
<P>
Market City Caffe, 33 S. Fair Oaks, Pasadena. (818) 568-0203. Style: 
Neighborhood Italian with ample antipasto bar. Setting: Pseudo-market. 
Recommended dishes: Pizza portofino; grilled veal chop; tirami su. Cost per 
person: $10-$25. 
</P>
<P>
Menage, 119 E. Colorado Blvd., Pasadena. (818) 568-9164. Style: A little Cajun; 
a little California, a little Southwestern. Setting: A little disco; a little 
backgammon; a little noisy. Recommended dishes: Ceviche; shrimp etouffee; 
lobster ravioli. Cost per person: $15-$30. 
</P>
<P>
Parkway Grill, 510 S. Arroyo Pkwy., Pasadena. (818) 795-1001. Style: Trendy 
Spago copycat. Setting: Bricks and boards. Recommended dishes: Sonoma lamb 
salad; applewood smoked chicken; pizza with four cheeses. Cost per person: 
$20-$35. 
</P>
<P>
Restaurant Shiro, 1505 Mission St., South Pasadena (818) 799-4774. Style: 
Franco-Japanese for fish-loving foodies. Setting: Simple storefront. 
Recommended dishes: Chinese ravioli with shrimp and salmon mousse; Catfish in 
Japanese ponzu sauce; seafood salad. Cost per person: $15-$25. Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
