* AIN'T THAT A SHAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Dennis Hunt 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Most of this album is as bad as you'd expect -- but not for the reasons you'd 
expect. Osmond has the reputation for being a bland, soulless singer. His 
vocals, however, aren't the main flaw in this collection of rather dreary pop 
songs. The problem is primarily inferior material and thoroughly unimaginative, 
one-dimensional production -- particularly on the up-tempo songs. His Top 5 
pop/dance hit "Soldier of Love" works because of the punchy arrangement -- and 
in spite of his tepid vocals. But, except for a few lapses, his singing is 
generally passable, and on a few ballads even praiseworthy, showing some 
strength and honest feeling. With the right material and production, Osmond 
just might turn out a very good pop album. Dennis Hunt 
</P>
