<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHARING CREDITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Leon Whiteson's recent story ("Chairs on Exhibit: The Bottom Line," May 15) 
kindly described me as the designer of the Evolutionary Chair, which was part 
of the recent "Chair as Art" display at the Gallery of Art on Main Street in 
Santa Monica. To be fair, my colleagues at Gwynne Pugh and Associates -- Gwynne 
Pugh and James Dove -- also should receive the credit due them for their work 
on that piece. 
</P>
<P>
LARRY SCARPA 
</P>
<P>
Santa Monica 
</P>
