<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two San Joaquin Valley counties were accused in Fresno of violating the federal 
Clean Air Act by failing to meet air quality standards. Three environmentalist 
groups -- Citizens for a Healthy Environment, Sierra Club and Kern County 
Valley Action Network -- filed suit in U.S. District Court, calling for the 
federal Environmental Protection Agency to impose sanctions on Kern and Fresno 
counties for failing to meet a 1987 compliance deadline. The suit alleges that 
the two counties have "consistently violated the federal health standards for 
ozone." 
</P>
