<HEADLINE>
<P>
IRAN ASSAILS SAUDIS AGAIN OVER PILGRIMAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NICOSIA, Cyprus 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Iran on Saturday renewed attacks on Saudi Arabia, saying the Saudis have banned 
its pilgrims from Mecca, and announced a "week of antipathy toward unbelievers" 
to coincide with next month's event. Mohammed Khatami, Islamic guidance 
minister, said programs have been arranged for July 5-11 to show Iran's 
determination to voice its anti-superpower stance. 
</P>
