<HEADLINE>
<P>
DISPUTE ON HOTEL TAB BRINGS ARREST OF THEFT SUSPECTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PALATINE, Ill. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man and woman who refused to pay a hotel bill were jailed Friday on charges 
of robbing a Milwaukee bank. 
</P>
<P>
The two were arrested after police found a bag containing "a substantial 
amount" of money, some of it tainted with a red dye banks use to identify 
stolen money. 
</P>
<P>
Karen Ray and Rufus Patterson had refused to pay their bill at the Quality Inn, 
so employees called police. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA060489-0122 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 65842 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
June 4, 1989, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
