<HEADLINE>
<P>
EXPLOSIONS AT GUNPOWDER PLANT INJURE 18, DESTROY 3 BUILDINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated PressDrawing 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Explosions leveled three buildings at a gunpowder plant in Roxbury Township, 
N.J., Saturday, injuring at least 18 people, blowing out windows in nearby 
towns and shaking houses up to 13 miles away, authorities said. The cause of 
the blast was unknown. The explosions at the Hercules Powder Inc. plant knocked 
down trees, tore off doors and damaged many homes and about 80% of the 
businesses in this township, about 40 miles west of New York City, officials 
said. Three of about 40 buildings at the complex were destroyed and several 
were damaged, a company manager said. Twelve people were treated and released 
at a local hospital. Three were admitted with injuries ranging from back pains 
to a concussion. All werein stable condition, supervisor Barbara Treverrow 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Best said the material that exploded Saturday was a smokeless propellant used 
in shotgun shells. 
</P>
<P>
He said that to limit damage, the plant is divided into compartments that each 
contain no more than 1,000 pounds of gunpowder. The gunpowder plant is located 
in a somewhat isolated ara near several small towns. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
