<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMENTS ON LETTER ABOUT JURY DUTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Having read Judy Perry's letter in the May 28 Orange County Edition of The 
Times, "How Jury Duty Alters View of Legal System," I understand her 
disappointment with the vacuous, would-be jury panelists surrounding her. 
</P>
<P>
I am reminded, therefore, of the old joke regarding anyone facing justice 
before the American legal system. It goes like this: "Would you want your life 
in the hands of 12 people who weren't smart enough to get out of jury duty?" 
</P>
<P>
I rest my case. 
</P>
<P>
STEPHEN C. LEE 
</P>
<P>
La Habra 
</P>
</TEXT>
