<HEADLINE>
<P>
COSTA RICA CLARIFICATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On behalf of the Costa Rica National Tourist Bureau I wish to express our 
gratitude for Geri Massion's article on Costa Rica ("Volcano Adds Touch of 
Drama to Costa Rica Trip," May 21). I do, however, wish to clarify the 
statement: "Eco Tours, an agency of the Costa Rica Tourist Board . . . " 
</P>
<P>
The Costa Rica Tourist Board is an Institution of the Government of Costa Rica 
and, as such, is responsible for tourism development and promotion of the 
country. It is totally untrue that Eco Tours is an agency of the Tourist Board, 
since we do not have (such an agency) and are expressly prohibited from doing 
so by our government. Our responsibilities lie in dealing impartially with all 
wholesalers who promote the country. 
</P>
<P>
LAUDENCIO CASTRO 
</P>
<P>
Executive Director 
</P>
<P>
Costa Rica National Tourist Bureau 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
