CELEBRITY RUNNERS RAISE RECORD AMOUNT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The tally is in, showing that a record-breaking $600,000 -- more than double 
1988's total -- was collected during this year's Los Angeles Marathon by the 
Celebrity Running Team, captained by Jack Scalia and sponsored by Great Earth 
Europlex. The pledges, raised by about 100 actors, athletes and other 
celebrities, will be distributed among the marathon's 26 official charities. 
