<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOUR TEEN-AGERS KILLED AS THEIR CAR SLAMS INTO WALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LANCASTER, Tex. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A sports car carrying four teen-agers who had just left a high school 
graduation rehearsal veered out of control and crashed into a wall in suburban 
Dallas, killing everyone inside, authorities said. Investigators said excessive 
speed might have been a factor in the Friday crash. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA060489-0177 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 65981 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
June 4, 1989, Sunday, Valley Edition 
</P>
