<TEXT>
<P>
Juan Antonio Samaranch, president of the International Olympic Committee, 
dismissed as "untruthful" claims by Ben Johnson's doctor that the IOC chief 
wanted to withhold news of the Canadian sprinter's failed doping test at the 
Seoul Olympics. 
</P>
<P>
A cover-up would have been impossible as 30 to 40 people, including members of 
the IOC's medical and executive commissions and the Canadian delegation, knew 
of the results of Johnson's tests, Samaranch told a Geneva newspaper. 
</P>
