<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: CAL LUTHERAN KICKER SIGNS WITH BEARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kent Sullivan, the second all-time leading punter in Cal Lutheran history, has 
signed with the Chicago Bears. 
</P>
<P>
In four years at Cal Lutheran, Sullivan had 240 punts for an average of 38.4 
yards. Also a kicker, Sullivan set school records for longest field goal (52 
yards) and longest punt (74 yards) last season. 
</P>
<P>
Sullivan, 25, is scheduled to report to the Bears' training camp in 
Platteville, Wis., on July 6. 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Northridge product Bryan Wagner was the Bears' punter last season, 
but he was claimed by the Cleveland Browns when the Bears left him on the 
unprotected list. 
</P>
<P>
John Tomac of Chatsworth finished 20th in the sixth stage of the Milk Run 
cycling race Saturday, covering the 106-mile Barnsley-to-Liverpool course in 
England in 4 hours, 1 minute, 18 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
Tomac stands ninth overall, 38 seconds behind Briton Nigel Bishop. Bishop was 
credited with the same time as Tomac on Saturday and has a composite time of 24 
hours, 40 minutes, 12 seconds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
