<HEADLINE>
<P>
APPARENT FALL FROM 2ND STORY KILLS TEXAN VISITING NEWPORT BEACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 24-year-old Texas man was fatally injured Saturday when he apparently fell 
off a second-story balcony while visiting friends in Newport Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Cleon Lee Warren, of Austin, had been visiting friends at a residence in the 
1700 block of West Balboa Avenue about 3 a.m. when he went onto the balcony to 
smoke a cigarette, Newport Beach Sgt. Gene Senecal said. 
</P>
<P>
When Warren had not returned after several minutes, someone went onto the 
balcony to look for him but saw him unconscious on the pavement, 18 feet below, 
Senecal said. 
</P>
<P>
Warren was taken to Hoag Hospital where he died of his injuries at 12:30 p.m. 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Senecal said police are investigating the death as an accident. It is still not 
known how Warren fell off the balcony, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Coroner's officials said an autopsy is scheduled today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
